It's unpleasant in my opinion, as a lifelong book reader. Spreading it out, as you put it, is for reader convience and clarity. It creates a rhythm and keys the reader in to a new person speaking without dialogue tags.

I have a preference for line breaks because I think it flows better. It depends though.
